                                "text": "Mr. Justice Brennan has two opinions for the Court to announce."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 4.69,
                        "stop": 113.165,
                        "byte_start": 95608,
                        "byte_stop": 529450,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15140,
                            "name": "William J. Brennan, Jr.",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/william_j_brennan_jr",
                            "last_name": "Brennan",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2786,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": -416862000,
                                    "date_end": 648450000,
                                    "appointing_president": "Dwight D. Eisenhower",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2786"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32778,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 56873,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/william_j_brennan.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 12330,
                            "identifier": "william_j_brennan_jr"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 4.69,
                                "stop": 15.477,
                                "byte_start": 95608,
                                "byte_stop": 138762,
                                "text": "The first of the cases is Number 73-370, National Labor Relations Board versus the Food Store Employees Union."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 15.477,
                                "stop": 39.748,
                                "byte_start": 138762,
                                "byte_stop": 235833,
                                "text": "In this case, the National Labor Relations Board rejected the argument of respondent Union, the charging party in this unfair labor practice case, that the remedy ordered by the Board should include a provision, ordering the employer to reimburse the Union for its litigation expenses."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 39.748,
                                "stop": 75.942,
                                "byte_start": 235833,
                                "byte_stop": 380656,
                                "text": "The Union sought review of that refusal in the Court of Appeals for the District of Colombia circuit, and I have \u201cagreed\u201d with the Board, but instead of remanding the case to the Board for further consideration, the Court itself enlarged the Board\u0027s order to add a provision requiring the employer to pay not only the Union but also the Board the costs and expenses incurred by each of them in connection with the litigation."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 75.942,
                                "stop": 90.857,
                                "byte_start": 380656,
                                "byte_stop": 440320,
                                "text": "The Courts of Appeals, under Sections 10 (e) and (f) of the Act, have authority, and I quote the statue, to \u201cmake and enter a decree modifying, and enforcing as so modified\u201d Board orders."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 90.857,
                                "stop": 105.778,
                                "byte_start": 440320,
                                "byte_stop": 499984,
                                "text": "What we hold in this case is the Court of Appeals action in enlarging the Board\u0027s remedies for the reasons expressed in our opinion, was an improper exercise of that authority."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 105.778,
                                "stop": 113.165,
                                "byte_start": 499984,
                                "byte_stop": 529450,
                                "text": "We, therefore, unanimously reverse so much of the Court of Appeals judgment, as enlarged the Board\u0027s order."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    },
